            "title": "UBS Vice Chairman to Retire",
            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text\"><p>\n  By Adria Calatayud </p><br/><p>\n  UBS Group said Lukas Gaehwiler, vice chairman of its board, is retiring, and proposed compliance chief Markus Ronner as his successor. </p><!-- Article --><p>\n\n  The Swiss bank said Friday that Gaehwiler won't stand for re-election at next year's annual general meeting as he decided to retire after a 45-year career in banking. Gaehwiler played a key role in the integration of Credit Suisse, having served as its final chair, UBS said. </p><p>\n\n  The bank said it would nominate Markus Ronner, who is currently the group's chief compliance and governance officer, as new board member and vice chairman. A successor for Ronner will be announced separately, UBS said. </p><br/><p>\n  Write to Adria Calatayud at adria.calatayud@wsj.com </p><br/><p>\n  (END) Dow Jones Newswires</p><p>\n\n  10-24-25 0116ET</p></div>",
